isisMIB.name: isisMIB
isisMIB.organization: IETF IS-IS for IP Internets Working Group
isisMIB.contactinfo: IS-IS for IP Internets working Group http://www.ietf.org/html.charters/isis-charter.html isis-wg@ietf.org Jeff Parker Department of Computer Science Middlebury College, Middlebury, Vermont 05753 jeffp at middlbury dot edu
isisMIB.description: This document describes a management information base for the IS-IS Routing protocol, as described in ISO 10589, when it is used to construct routing tables for IP networks, as described in RFC 1195. This document is based on a 1994 IETF document by Chris Gunner. This version has been modified to include current syntax, to exclude portions of the protocol that are not relevant to IP, and to add management support for current practice. Copyright (C) The Internet Society (2006). This version of this MIB module is part of RFC 4444; see the RFC itself for full legal notices.

IsisOSINSAddress.name: IsisOSINSAddress
IsisOSINSAddress.description: OSI Network Service Address, e.g., NSAP, SNPA, or Network Entity Title

IsisSystemID.name: IsisSystemID
IsisSystemID.description: The ID for an Intermediate System. This should be unique within a network, and is included in all PDUs originated by an Intermediate System. The protocol does not place any meanings upon the bits, other than using ordering to break ties in electing a Designated IS on a LAN.

IsisLinkStatePDUID.name: IsisLinkStatePDUID
IsisLinkStatePDUID.description: The 8-byte Link State PDU (LSP) ID, consisting of the 6-byte SystemID of the originating IS; a one-byte PseudoNode ID, which is 0 unless the LSP represents the topology of a LAN; and a one-byte LSP fragment number that is issued in sequence, starting with 0. Non-zero PseudoNode IDs need to be unique to the IS but need not match the IfIndex.

IsisAdminState.name: IsisAdminState
IsisAdminState.description: Type used in enabling and disabling a row.

IsisLSPBuffSize.name: IsisLSPBuffSize
IsisLSPBuffSize.description: Integer sub-range for maximum LSP size.

IsisSupportedProtocol.name: IsisSupportedProtocol
IsisSupportedProtocol.description: Types of network protocol supported by Integrated IS-IS. The values for ISO8473 and IP are those registered for these protocols in ISO TR9577.

IsisDefaultMetric.name: IsisDefaultMetric
IsisDefaultMetric.description: Integer sub-range for default metric for single hop. ISO 10589 provides for 4 types of metric. Only the 'default' metric is used in practice.

IsisWideMetric.name: IsisWideMetric
IsisWideMetric.description: Wide metric for IS Neighbors. ISO 10589 provides a 6-bit metric. Traffic Engineering extensions provide 24-bit metrics.

IsisFullMetric.name: IsisFullMetric
IsisFullMetric.description: Full metric for IP Routes. Traffic Engineering extensions provide 32-bit metrics.

IsisMetricType.name: IsisMetricType
IsisMetricType.description: Is this an Internal or External Metric?

IsisMetricStyle.name: IsisMetricStyle
IsisMetricStyle.description: Do we use RFC 1195 style metrics or wide metrics?

IsisPDUHeader.name: IsisPDUHeader
IsisPDUHeader.description: A block to contain the header from a PDU.

IsisUnsigned16TC.name: IsisUnsigned16TC
IsisUnsigned16TC.description: An Unsigned32 further restricted to 16 bits. Note that the ASN.1 BER encoding may still require 24 bits for some values.

IsisUnsigned8TC.name: IsisUnsigned8TC
IsisUnsigned8TC.description: An Unsigned32 further restricted to 8 bits. Note that the ASN.1 BER encoding may still require 16 bits for some values.

isisSysVersion.name: isisSysVersion
isisSysVersion.description: The version number of the IS-IS protocol that is implemented.

isisSysLevelType.name: isisSysLevelType
isisSysLevelType.description: At which levels is the Intermediate System running? This object may not be modified when the isisSysAdminState variable is in state 'on' for this Intermediate System. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisSysID.name: isisSysID
isisSysID.description: The ID for this Intermediate System. This value is appended to each of the area addresses to form the Network Entity Titles. The derivation of a value for this object is implementation specific. Some implementations may automatically assign values and not permit an SNMP write, while others may require the value to be set manually. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisSysMaxPathSplits.name: isisSysMaxPathSplits
isisSysMaxPathSplits.description: Maximum number of paths with equal routing metric value which it is permitted to split between. This object may not be modified when the isisSysAdminState variable is in state 'on' for this Intermediate System. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisSysMaxLSPGenInt.name: isisSysMaxLSPGenInt
isisSysMaxLSPGenInt.description: Maximum interval, in seconds, between generated LSPs by this Intermediate System. This object follows the ResettingTimer behavior. The value must be greater than any value configured for isisSysLevelMinLSPGenInt, and should be at least 300 seconds less than isisSysMaxAge. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisSysPollESHelloRate.name: isisSysPollESHelloRate
isisSysPollESHelloRate.description: The value, in seconds, to be used for the suggested ES configuration timer in ISH PDUs when soliciting the ES configuration. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisSysWaitTime.name: isisSysWaitTime
isisSysWaitTime.description: Number of seconds to delay in state 'waiting' before entering the state 'on'. This object follows the ResettingTimer behavior. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisSysAdminState.name: isisSysAdminState
isisSysAdminState.description: The administrative state of this Intermediate System. Setting this object to the value 'on' when its current value is 'off' enables the Intermediate System. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisSysL2toL1Leaking.name: isisSysL2toL1Leaking
isisSysL2toL1Leaking.description: If true, allow the router to leak L2 routes into L1. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisSysMaxAge.name: isisSysMaxAge
isisSysMaxAge.description: Value to place in RemainingLifeTime field of the LSPs we generate. This should be at least 300 seconds greater than isisSysMaxLSPGenInt. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisSysReceiveLSPBufferSize.name: isisSysReceiveLSPBufferSize
isisSysReceiveLSPBufferSize.description: Size of the largest buffer we are designed or configured to store. This should be at least as big as the maximum isisSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize supported by the system. If resources allow, we will store and flood LSPs larger than isisSysReceiveLSPBufferSize, as this can help avoid problems in networks with different values for isisSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisSysProtSupported.name: isisSysProtSupported
isisSysProtSupported.description: This attribute contains the set of protocols supported by this Intermediate System.

isisSysNotificationEnable.name: isisSysNotificationEnable
isisSysNotificationEnable.description: If this object is set to true(1), then it enables the emission of IS-IS Notifications. If it is set to false(2), these notifications are not sent. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisManAreaAddrTable.name: isisManAreaAddrTable
isisManAreaAddrTable.description: The set of manual area addresses configured on this Intermediate System. At least one row in which the value of isisManAreaAddrExistState is active must be present. The maximum number of rows in this table for which the object isisManAreaAddrExistState has the value active is 3. An attempt to create more than 3 rows of isisManAreaAddrEntry with state 'active' in one instance of the IS-IS protocol should return inconsistentValue.

isisManAreaAddrEntry.name: isisManAreaAddrEntry
isisManAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one area address manually configured on this system. Dynamically created rows MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisManAreaAddr.name: isisManAreaAddr
isisManAreaAddr.description: A manually configured area address for this system. Note: An index for the entry {1, {49.0001} active} in this table would be the ordered pair (1, (0x03 0x49 0x00 0x01)), as the length of an octet string is part of the OID.

isisManAreaAddrExistState.name: isisManAreaAddrExistState
isisManAreaAddrExistState.description: The state of the isisManAreaAddrEntry. If the isisSysAdminState for this Intermediate System is 'on' and an attempt is made to set this object to the value 'destroy' or 'notInService' when this is the only isisManAreaAddrEntry in state 'active' for this Intermediate System should return inconsistentValue. A row entry cannot be modified when the value of this object is 'active'.

isisAreaAddrTable.name: isisAreaAddrTable
isisAreaAddrTable.description: The union of the sets of area addresses reported in all Level 1 LSPs with fragment number zero generated by this Intermediate System, or received from other Intermediate Systems that are reachable via Level 1 routing.

isisAreaAddrEntry.name: isisAreaAddrEntry
isisAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one area address reported in a Level 1 LSP generated or received by this Intermediate System. Dynamically learned rows do not survive an agent reboot.

isisAreaAddr.name: isisAreaAddr
isisAreaAddr.description: An area address reported in a Level 1 LSP.

isisSummAddrTable.name: isisSummAddrTable
isisSummAddrTable.description: The set of IP summary addresses to use in forming summary TLVs originated by this Intermediate System. An administrator may use a summary address to combine and modify IP Reachability announcements. If the Intermediate system can reach any subset of the summary address, the summary address MUST be announced instead, at the configured metric.

isisSummAddrEntry.name: isisSummAddrEntry
isisSummAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one IP summary address. Dynamically created rows MUST survive an agent reboot. Implementers need to be aware that if the total number of elements (octets or sub-identifiers) in isisSummAddress and isisSummAddrPrefixLen is too great, then OIDs of column instances in this table will have more than 128 subidentifiers and cannot be accessed using SNMPv1, SNMPv2c, or SNMPv3.

isisSummAddressType.name: isisSummAddressType
isisSummAddressType.description: The Type of IP address for this summary address.

isisSummAddress.name: isisSummAddress
isisSummAddress.description: The IP Address value for this summary address. The address must not contain any set host bits (bits set after the address prefix determined by isisSummAddrPrefixLen). The type of this address is determined by the value of the isisSummAddressType object.

isisSummAddrPrefixLen.name: isisSummAddrPrefixLen
isisSummAddrPrefixLen.description: The Length of the IP NetMask for this summary address. The values for the index objects isisSummAddress and isisSummAddrPrefixLen must be consistent. When the value of isisSummAddress (excluding the zone index, if one is present) is x, then the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the mask formed from the corresponding index object isisSummAddrPrefixLen MUST be equal to x. If not, then the index pair is not consistent, and an inconsistentName error must be returned on SET or CREATE requests.

isisSummAddrExistState.name: isisSummAddrExistState
isisSummAddrExistState.description: The existence state of this summary address. Support for 'createAndWait' and 'notInService' is not required. A row entry cannot be modified when the value of this object is 'active'.

isisSummAddrMetric.name: isisSummAddrMetric
isisSummAddrMetric.description: The metric value to announce this summary address within LSPs generated by this system.

isisSummAddrFullMetric.name: isisSummAddrFullMetric
isisSummAddrFullMetric.description: The wide metric value to announce this summary address within LSPs generated by this system.

isisRedistributeAddrTable.name: isisRedistributeAddrTable
isisRedistributeAddrTable.description: This table provides criteria to decide if a route should be leaked from L2 to L1 when Domain Wide Prefix leaking is enabled. Addresses that match the summary mask in the table MUST be announced at L1 by routers when isisSysL2toL1Leaking is enabled. Routes that fall into the ranges specified are announced as is, without being summarized. Routes that do not match a summary mask are not announced.

isisRedistributeAddrEntry.name: isisRedistributeAddrEntry
isisRedistributeAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one configured IP summary address to manage leaking L2 addresses into L1. Dynamically created rows MUST survive an agent reboot. Implementers need to be aware that if the total number of elements (octets or sub-identifiers) in isisRedistributeAddrAddress and isisRedistributeAddrPrefixLen is too great, then OIDs of column instances in this table will have more than 128 subidentifiers and cannot be accessed using SNMPv1, SNMPv2c, or SNMPv3.

isisRedistributeAddrType.name: isisRedistributeAddrType
isisRedistributeAddrType.description: The Type of IP address for this summary address.

isisRedistributeAddrAddress.name: isisRedistributeAddrAddress
isisRedistributeAddrAddress.description: The IP Address value for this summary address. The type of this address is determined by the value of the isisRedistributeAddrType object. The address must not contain any set host bits - bits set after the address prefix determined by isisRedistributeAddrPrefixLen.

isisRedistributeAddrPrefixLen.name: isisRedistributeAddrPrefixLen
isisRedistributeAddrPrefixLen.description: The Length of the IP NetMask for this summary address. The values for the index objects isisRedistributeAddrAddress and isisRedistributeAddrPrefixLen must be consistent. When the value of isisRedistributeAddrAddress (excluding the zone index, if one is present) is x, then the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the mask formed from the corresponding index object isisRedistributeAddrPrefixLen MUST be equal to x. If not, then the index pair is not consistent, and an inconsistentName error must be returned on SET or CREATE requests.

isisRedistributeAddrExistState.name: isisRedistributeAddrExistState
isisRedistributeAddrExistState.description: The existence state of this summary address. Support for createAndWait and notInService is not required. A row entry cannot be modified when the value of this object is 'active'.

isisRouterTable.name: isisRouterTable
isisRouterTable.description: The set of hostnames and router ID.

isisRouterEntry.name: isisRouterEntry
isisRouterEntry.description: Each entry tracks information about one Intermediate System at one level. Dynamically learned rows do not survive an agent reboot.

isisRouterSysID.name: isisRouterSysID
isisRouterSysID.description: The System ID of the Intermediate System.

isisRouterLevel.name: isisRouterLevel
isisRouterLevel.description: The level at which the information about this Intermediate System was received.

isisRouterHostName.name: isisRouterHostName
isisRouterHostName.description: The hostname listed in the LSP, or a zero-length string if none.

isisRouterID.name: isisRouterID
isisRouterID.description: The Router ID found in the LSP, or zero if none.

isisSysLevelTable.name: isisSysLevelTable
isisSysLevelTable.description: Level specific information about the System.

isisSysLevelEntry.name: isisSysLevelEntry
isisSysLevelEntry.description: Each row describes variables configured for Area or Domain. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisSysLevelIndex.name: isisSysLevelIndex
isisSysLevelIndex.description: The level that this entry describes.

isisSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize.name: isisSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize
isisSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize.description: The maximum size of LSPs and SNPs originated by this Intermediate System at this level. This object may not be modified when the isisSysAdminState variable is in state 'on' for this Intermediate System.

isisSysLevelMinLSPGenInt.name: isisSysLevelMinLSPGenInt
isisSysLevelMinLSPGenInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between successive generation of LSPs with the same LSPID at this level by this Intermediate System.

isisSysLevelState.name: isisSysLevelState
isisSysLevelState.description: The state of the database at this level. The value 'off' indicates that IS-IS is not active at this level. The value 'on' indicates that IS-IS is active at this level and is not overloaded. The value 'waiting' indicates a database that is low on an essential resource, such as memory. The administrator may force the state to 'overloaded' by setting the object isisSysLevelSetOverload. If the state is 'waiting' or 'overloaded', we originate LSPs with the overload bit set.

isisSysLevelSetOverload.name: isisSysLevelSetOverload
isisSysLevelSetOverload.description: Administratively set the overload bit for the level. The overload bit MUST continue to be set if the implementation runs out of memory, independent of this variable. It may also be set manually independent of this variable, using the isisSysLevelSetOverloadUntil object.

isisSysLevelSetOverloadUntil.name: isisSysLevelSetOverloadUntil
isisSysLevelSetOverloadUntil.units: Seconds until clearing manually set Overload Bit
isisSysLevelSetOverloadUntil.description: If this object is non-zero, the overload bit is set at this level when the isisSysAdminState variable goes to state 'on' for this Intermediate System. The overload bit remains set for isisSysLevelSetOverloadUntil seconds. When isisSysLevelSetOverloadUntil seconds have elapsed, the overload flag remains set if the implementation has run out of memory, or if it is set manually using the isisSysLevelSetOverload object. If isisSysLevelSetOverload is false, the system clears the overload bit when isisSysLevelSetOverloadUntil seconds have elapsed, if the system has not run out of memory.

isisSysLevelMetricStyle.name: isisSysLevelMetricStyle
isisSysLevelMetricStyle.description: Which style of metric do we generate in our LSPs at this level?

isisSysLevelSPFConsiders.name: isisSysLevelSPFConsiders
isisSysLevelSPFConsiders.description: Which style of metric do we consider in our SPF computation at this level?

isisSysLevelTEEnabled.name: isisSysLevelTEEnabled
isisSysLevelTEEnabled.description: Do we do Traffic Engineering at this level?

isisNextCircIndex.name: isisNextCircIndex
isisNextCircIndex.description: This object is used to assist a management application in creating new rows in the isisCircTable. If it is possible to create a new instance of isisCircEntry, then this object will contain a non-zero value that is not in use as the index of any row in the isisCircTable. The network manager reads the value of this object and then (if the value read is non-zero) attempts to create the corresponding instance of isisCircEntry. If the set request fails with the code 'inconsistentValue', then the process must be repeated; if the set request succeeds, then the agent will change the value of this object according to an implementation-specific algorithm.

isisCircTable.name: isisCircTable
isisCircTable.description: The table of circuits used by this Intermediate System.

isisCircEntry.name: isisCircEntry
isisCircEntry.description: An isisCircEntry exists for each circuit configured for Integrated IS-IS on this system. Dynamically created rows MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisCircIndex.name: isisCircIndex
isisCircIndex.description: An index used to uniquely identify this circuit. When creating a row in this table, the isisNextCircIndex object should be retrieved, and its value should be specified as the value of this index using a SET operation. A retrieved value of zero(0) indicates that no rows can be created at this time.

isisCircIfIndex.name: isisCircIfIndex
isisCircIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex for the interface to which this circuit corresponds. This object cannot be modified after creation.

isisCircAdminState.name: isisCircAdminState
isisCircAdminState.description: The administrative state of the circuit.

isisCircExistState.name: isisCircExistState
isisCircExistState.description: The existence state of this circuit. Setting the state to 'notInService' halts the generation and processing of IS-IS protocol PDUs on this circuit. Setting the state to destroy will also erase any configuration associated with the circuit. Support for 'createAndWait' and 'notInService' is not required. A row entry cannot be modified when the value of this object is 'active'.

isisCircType.name: isisCircType
isisCircType.description: The type of the circuit. This object follows the ReplaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior. The type specified must be compatible with the type of the interface defined by the value of isisCircIfIndex.

isisCircExtDomain.name: isisCircExtDomain
isisCircExtDomain.description: If true, suppress normal transmission of and interpretation of Intra-domain IS-IS PDUs on this circuit.

isisCircLevelType.name: isisCircLevelType
isisCircLevelType.description: Indicates which type of packets will be sent and accepted on this circuit. The values set will be saved, but the values used will be modified by the settings of isisSysLevelType. Thus, if the isisSysTpe is level2 and the isisCircLevelType for a circuit is level1, the circuit will not send or receive IS-IS packets. This object follows the ReplaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior.

isisCircPassiveCircuit.name: isisCircPassiveCircuit
isisCircPassiveCircuit.description: Should we include this interface in LSPs, even if it is not running the IS-IS Protocol?

isisCircMeshGroupEnabled.name: isisCircMeshGroupEnabled
isisCircMeshGroupEnabled.description: Is this port a member of a mesh group, or is it blocked? Circuits in the same mesh group act as a virtual multiaccess network. LSPs seen on one circuit in a mesh group will not be flooded to another circuit in the same mesh group.

isisCircMeshGroup.name: isisCircMeshGroup
isisCircMeshGroup.description: Circuits in the same mesh group act as a virtual multiaccess network. LSPs seen on one circuit in a mesh group will not be flooded to another circuit in the same mesh group. If isisCircMeshGroupEnabled is inactive or blocked, this value is ignored.

isisCircSmallHellos.name: isisCircSmallHellos
isisCircSmallHellos.description: Can we send unpadded hellos on LAN circuits? False means the LAN Hellos must be padded. Implementations should allow the administrator to read this value. An implementation need not be able to support unpadded hellos to be conformant.

isisCircLastUpTime.name: isisCircLastUpTime
isisCircLastUpTime.description: How long the circuit has been enabled, measured in hundredths of seconds since the last re-initialization of the network management subsystem; 0 if the circuit has never been 'on'.

isisCirc3WayEnabled.name: isisCirc3WayEnabled
isisCirc3WayEnabled.description: Is this circuit enabled to run 3Way handshake?

isisCircExtendedCircID.name: isisCircExtendedCircID
isisCircExtendedCircID.description: The value to be used as the extended circuit ID in 3Way handshake. This value is only used if isisCirc3WayEnabled is true, and it must be unique across all circuits on this IS.

isisCircLevelTable.name: isisCircLevelTable
isisCircLevelTable.description: Level specific information about circuits used by IS-IS.

isisCircLevelEntry.name: isisCircLevelEntry
isisCircLevelEntry.description: An isisCircLevelEntry exists for each level on each circuit configured for Integrated IS-IS on this system. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisCircLevelIndex.name: isisCircLevelIndex
isisCircLevelIndex.description: The level that this entry describes.

isisCircLevelMetric.name: isisCircLevelMetric
isisCircLevelMetric.description: The metric value of this circuit for this level.

isisCircLevelWideMetric.name: isisCircLevelWideMetric
isisCircLevelWideMetric.description: The wide metric value of this circuit for this level.

isisCircLevelISPriority.name: isisCircLevelISPriority
isisCircLevelISPriority.description: The priority for becoming the LAN-Designated Intermediate System at this level.

isisCircLevelIDOctet.name: isisCircLevelIDOctet
isisCircLevelIDOctet.description: A one-byte identifier for the circuit selected by the Intermediate System. On point-to-point circuits, the value is used as the Local Circuit ID in point-to-point IIH PDUs transmitted on this circuit. In this case, values of isisCircLevelIDOctet do not need to be unique. For broadcast circuits, the value is used to generate the LAN ID that will be used if this Intermediate System is elected as the Designated IS on this circuit. The value is required to differ on LANs where the Intermediate System is the Designated Intermediate System.

isisCircLevelID.name: isisCircLevelID
isisCircLevelID.description: On a point-to-point circuit with a fully initialized adjacency to a peer IS, the value of this object is the circuit ID negotiated during adjacency initialization. On a point to point circuit without such an adjacency, the value is the concatenation of the local system ID and the one-byte isisCircLevelIDOctet for this circuit, i.e., the value that would be proposed for the circuit ID. On other circuit types, the value returned is the zero- length OCTET STRING.

isisCircLevelDesIS.name: isisCircLevelDesIS
isisCircLevelDesIS.description: The ID of the LAN-Designated Intermediate System on this circuit at this level. If, for any reason, this system is not partaking in the relevant Designated Intermediate System election process, then the value returned is the zero-length OCTET STRING.

isisCircLevelHelloMultiplier.name: isisCircLevelHelloMultiplier
isisCircLevelHelloMultiplier.description: This value is multiplied by the corresponding HelloTimer, and the result in seconds (rounded up) is used as the holding time in transmitted hellos, to be used by receivers of hello packets from this IS.

isisCircLevelHelloTimer.name: isisCircLevelHelloTimer
isisCircLevelHelloTimer.description: Maximum period, in milliseconds, between IIH PDUs on multiaccess networks at this level for LANs. The value at L1 is used as the period between Hellos on L1L2 point-to-point circuits. Setting this value at level 2 on an L1L2 point-to-point circuit will result in an error of InconsistentValue. This object follows the ResettingTimer behavior.

isisCircLevelDRHelloTimer.name: isisCircLevelDRHelloTimer
isisCircLevelDRHelloTimer.description: Period, in milliseconds, between Hello PDUs on multiaccess networks when this IS is the Designated Intermediate System. This object follows the ResettingTimer behavior.

isisCircLevelLSPThrottle.name: isisCircLevelLSPThrottle
isisCircLevelLSPThrottle.description: Minimal interval of time, in milliseconds, between transmissions of LSPs on an interface at this level.

isisCircLevelMinLSPRetransInt.name: isisCircLevelMinLSPRetransInt
isisCircLevelMinLSPRetransInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between re-transmission of an LSP at this level. This object follows the ResettingTimer behavior. Note that isisCircLevelLSPThrottle controls how fast we send back-to-back LSPs. This variable controls how fast we re-send the same LSP.

isisCircLevelCSNPInterval.name: isisCircLevelCSNPInterval
isisCircLevelCSNPInterval.description: Interval of time, in seconds, between periodic transmission of a complete set of CSNPs on multiaccess networks if this router is the designated router at this level. This object follows the ResettingTimer behavior.

isisCircLevelPartSNPInterval.name: isisCircLevelPartSNPInterval
isisCircLevelPartSNPInterval.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between sending Partial Sequence Number PDUs at this level. This object follows the ResettingTimer behavior.

isisSystemCounterTable.name: isisSystemCounterTable
isisSystemCounterTable.description: System-wide counters for this Intermediate System.

isisSysStatLevel.name: isisSysStatLevel
isisSysStatLevel.description: The level that this entry describes.

isisSysStatCorrLSPs.name: isisSysStatCorrLSPs
isisSysStatCorrLSPs.description: Number of corrupted in-memory LSPs detected. LSPs received from the wire with a bad checksum are silently dropped and are not counted. LSPs received from the wire with parse errors are counted by isisSysStatLSPErrors.

isisSysStatAuthTypeFails.name: isisSysStatAuthTypeFails
isisSysStatAuthTypeFails.units: Number of frames with authentication type mismatches
isisSysStatAuthTypeFails.description: The number of authentication type mismatches recognized by this Intermediate System.

isisSysStatAuthFails.name: isisSysStatAuthFails
isisSysStatAuthFails.units: Number of frames with authentication key failures
isisSysStatAuthFails.description: The number of authentication key failures recognized by this Intermediate System.

isisSysStatLSPDbaseOloads.name: isisSysStatLSPDbaseOloads
isisSysStatLSPDbaseOloads.description: Number of times the LSP database has become overloaded.

isisSysStatManAddrDropFromAreas.name: isisSysStatManAddrDropFromAreas
isisSysStatManAddrDropFromAreas.description: Number of times a manual address has been dropped from the area.

isisSysStatAttmptToExMaxSeqNums.name: isisSysStatAttmptToExMaxSeqNums
isisSysStatAttmptToExMaxSeqNums.description: Number of times the IS has attempted to exceed the maximum sequence number.

isisSysStatSeqNumSkips.name: isisSysStatSeqNumSkips
isisSysStatSeqNumSkips.description: Number of times a sequence number skip has occurred.

isisSysStatOwnLSPPurges.name: isisSysStatOwnLSPPurges
isisSysStatOwnLSPPurges.description: Number of times a zero-aged copy of the system's own LSP is received from some other node.

isisSysStatIDFieldLenMismatches.name: isisSysStatIDFieldLenMismatches
isisSysStatIDFieldLenMismatches.units: Number of frames with ID length mismatches
isisSysStatIDFieldLenMismatches.description: Number of times a PDU is received with a different value for ID field length from that of the receiving system.

isisSysStatSPFRuns.name: isisSysStatSPFRuns
isisSysStatSPFRuns.description: Number of times we ran SPF at this level.

isisSysStatLSPErrors.name: isisSysStatLSPErrors
isisSysStatLSPErrors.units: Number of frames with errors that we have received
isisSysStatLSPErrors.description: Number of LSPs with errors we have received.

isisCircuitCounterTable.name: isisCircuitCounterTable
isisCircuitCounterTable.description: Circuit specific counters for this Intermediate System.

isisCircuitCounterEntry.name: isisCircuitCounterEntry
isisCircuitCounterEntry.description: An isisCircuitCounterEntry exists for each circuit used by Integrated IS-IS on this system.

isisCircuitType.name: isisCircuitType
isisCircuitType.description: What type of circuit saw these counts? The point-to-point Hello PDU includes both L1 and L2, and ISs form a single adjacency on point-to-point links. Thus, we combine counts on point-to-point links into one group.

isisCircAdjChanges.name: isisCircAdjChanges
isisCircAdjChanges.description: The number of times an adjacency state change has occurred on this circuit.

isisCircNumAdj.name: isisCircNumAdj
isisCircNumAdj.description: The number of adjacencies on this circuit.

isisCircInitFails.name: isisCircInitFails
isisCircInitFails.description: The number of times initialization of this circuit has failed. This counts events such as PPP NCP failures. Failures to form an adjacency are counted by isisCircRejAdjs.

isisCircRejAdjs.name: isisCircRejAdjs
isisCircRejAdjs.description: The number of times an adjacency has been rejected on this circuit.

isisCircIDFieldLenMismatches.name: isisCircIDFieldLenMismatches
isisCircIDFieldLenMismatches.units: Number of frames with ID field length mismatch
isisCircIDFieldLenMismatches.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with an ID field length different from that for this system has been received.

isisCircMaxAreaAddrMismatches.name: isisCircMaxAreaAddrMismatches
isisCircMaxAreaAddrMismatches.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with a max area address field different from that for this system has been received.

isisCircAuthTypeFails.name: isisCircAuthTypeFails
isisCircAuthTypeFails.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with an auth type field different from that for this system has been received.

isisCircAuthFails.name: isisCircAuthFails
isisCircAuthFails.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with the correct auth type has failed to pass authentication validation.

isisCircLANDesISChanges.name: isisCircLANDesISChanges
isisCircLANDesISChanges.description: The number of times the Designated IS has changed on this circuit at this level. If the circuit is point to point, this count is zero.

isisPacketCounterTable.name: isisPacketCounterTable
isisPacketCounterTable.description: Information about IS-IS protocol traffic at one level, on one circuit, in one direction.

isisPacketCounterEntry.name: isisPacketCounterEntry
isisPacketCounterEntry.description: Information about IS-IS protocol traffic at one level, on one circuit, in one direction.

isisPacketCountLevel.name: isisPacketCountLevel
isisPacketCountLevel.description: The level at which these PDU counts have been collected.

isisPacketCountDirection.name: isisPacketCountDirection
isisPacketCountDirection.description: Were we sending or receiving these PDUs?

isisPacketCountIIHello.name: isisPacketCountIIHello
isisPacketCountIIHello.units: Number of IS-IS Hellos frames seen in this direction at this level
isisPacketCountIIHello.description: The number of IS-IS Hello PDUs seen in this direction at this level. Point-to-Point IIH PDUs are counted at the lowest enabled level: at L1 on L1 or L1L2 circuits, and at L2 otherwise.

isisPacketCountISHello.name: isisPacketCountISHello
isisPacketCountISHello.units: Number of ES-IS frames seen in this direction at this level.
isisPacketCountISHello.description: The number of ES-IS Hello PDUs seen in this direction. ISH PDUs are counted at the lowest enabled level: at L1 on L1 or L1L2 circuits, and at L2 otherwise.

isisPacketCountESHello.name: isisPacketCountESHello
isisPacketCountESHello.units: Number of ES Hello frames seen in this direction at this level
isisPacketCountESHello.description: The number of ES Hello PDUs seen in this direction. ESH PDUs are counted at the lowest enabled level: at L1 on L1 or L1L2 circuits, and at L2 otherwise.

isisPacketCountLSP.name: isisPacketCountLSP
isisPacketCountLSP.units: Number of IS-IS LSP frames seen in this direction at this level
isisPacketCountLSP.description: The number of IS-IS LSPs seen in this direction at this level.

isisPacketCountCSNP.name: isisPacketCountCSNP
isisPacketCountCSNP.units: Number of IS-IS CSNP frames seen in this direction at this level
isisPacketCountCSNP.description: The number of IS-IS CSNPs seen in this direction at this level.

isisPacketCountPSNP.name: isisPacketCountPSNP
isisPacketCountPSNP.units: Number of IS-IS PSNP frames seen in this direction at this level
isisPacketCountPSNP.description: The number of IS-IS PSNPs seen in this direction at this level.

isisPacketCountUnknown.name: isisPacketCountUnknown
isisPacketCountUnknown.units: Number of unknown IS-IS frames seen at this level
isisPacketCountUnknown.description: The number of unknown IS-IS PDUs seen at this level.

isisISAdjTable.name: isisISAdjTable
isisISAdjTable.description: The table of adjacencies to Intermediate Systems.

isisISAdjEntry.name: isisISAdjEntry
isisISAdjEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one adjacency to an Intermediate System on this system. Dynamically learned rows do not survive an agent reboot.

isisISAdjIndex.name: isisISAdjIndex
isisISAdjIndex.description: A unique value identifying the IS adjacency from all other such adjacencies on this circuit. This value is automatically assigned by the system when the adjacency is created.

isisISAdj3WayState.name: isisISAdj3WayState
isisISAdj3WayState.description: The 3Way state of the adjacency. These are picked to match the historical on-the-wire representation of the 3Way state and are not intended to match isisISAdjState.

isisISAdjNeighSNPAAddress.name: isisISAdjNeighSNPAAddress
isisISAdjNeighSNPAAddress.description: The SNPA address of the neighboring system.

isisISAdjNeighSysType.name: isisISAdjNeighSysType
isisISAdjNeighSysType.description: The type of the neighboring system.

isisISAdjNeighSysID.name: isisISAdjNeighSysID
isisISAdjNeighSysID.description: The system ID of the neighboring Intermediate System.

isisISAdjNbrExtendedCircID.name: isisISAdjNbrExtendedCircID
isisISAdjNbrExtendedCircID.description: The 4-byte Extended Circuit ID learned from the Neighbor during 3-way handshake, or 0.

isisISAdjUsage.name: isisISAdjUsage
isisISAdjUsage.description: How is the adjacency used? On a point-to-point link, this might be level1and2, but on a LAN, the usage will be level1 on the adjacency between peers at L1, and level2 for the adjacency between peers at L2.

isisISAdjHoldTimer.name: isisISAdjHoldTimer
isisISAdjHoldTimer.description: The holding time, in seconds, for this adjacency. This value is based on received IIH PDUs and the elapsed time since receipt.

isisISAdjNeighPriority.name: isisISAdjNeighPriority
isisISAdjNeighPriority.description: Priority of the neighboring Intermediate System for becoming the Designated Intermediate System.

isisISAdjLastUpTime.name: isisISAdjLastUpTime
isisISAdjLastUpTime.description: When the adjacency most recently entered the state 'up', measured in hundredths of a second since the last re-initialization of the network management subsystem. Holds 0 if the adjacency has never been in state 'up'.

isisISAdjAreaAddrTable.name: isisISAdjAreaAddrTable
isisISAdjAreaAddrTable.description: This table contains the set of Area Addresses of neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

isisISAdjAreaAddrEntry.name: isisISAdjAreaAddrEntry
isisISAdjAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one Area Address reported by a neighboring Intermediate System in its IIH PDUs. Dynamically learned rows do not survive an agent reboot.

isisISAdjAreaAddrIndex.name: isisISAdjAreaAddrIndex
isisISAdjAreaAddrIndex.description: An index for the areas associated with one neighbor. This provides a simple way to walk the table.

isisISAdjAreaAddress.name: isisISAdjAreaAddress
isisISAdjAreaAddress.description: One Area Address as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

isisISAdjIPAddrTable.name: isisISAdjIPAddrTable
isisISAdjIPAddrTable.description: This table contains the set of IP Addresses of neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

isisISAdjIPAddrEntry.name: isisISAdjIPAddrEntry
isisISAdjIPAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one IP Address reported by a neighboring Intermediate System in its IIH PDUs. Dynamically learned rows do not survive an agent reboot.

isisISAdjIPAddrIndex.name: isisISAdjIPAddrIndex
isisISAdjIPAddrIndex.description: An index to this table that identifies the IP addresses to which this entry belongs.

isisISAdjIPAddrType.name: isisISAdjIPAddrType
isisISAdjIPAddrType.description: The type of one IP Address as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

isisISAdjIPAddrAddress.name: isisISAdjIPAddrAddress
isisISAdjIPAddrAddress.description: One IP Address as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor. The type of this address is determined by the value of the isisISAdjIPAddrType object.

isisISAdjProtSuppTable.name: isisISAdjProtSuppTable
isisISAdjProtSuppTable.description: This table contains the set of protocols supported by neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

isisISAdjProtSuppEntry.name: isisISAdjProtSuppEntry
isisISAdjProtSuppEntry.description: Each entry contains one protocol supported by a neighboring Intermediate System as reported in its IIH PDUs. Dynamically learned rows do not survive an agent reboot.

isisISAdjProtSuppProtocol.name: isisISAdjProtSuppProtocol
isisISAdjProtSuppProtocol.description: One supported protocol as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

isisRATable.name: isisRATable
isisRATable.description: The table of Reachable Addresses to NSAPs or Address Prefixes.

isisRAEntry.name: isisRAEntry
isisRAEntry.description: Each entry defines a configured Reachable Address to an NSAP or Address Prefix. Dynamically created rows MUST survive an agent reboot.

isisRAIndex.name: isisRAIndex
isisRAIndex.description: The identifier for this isisRAEntry. This value must be unique amongst all Reachable Addresses on the same parent Circuit.

isisRAExistState.name: isisRAExistState
isisRAExistState.description: The existence state of this Reachable Address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behaviors. Support for 'createAndWait' and 'notInService' is not required. A row entry cannot be modified when the value of this object is 'active'.

isisRAAdminState.name: isisRAAdminState
isisRAAdminState.description: The administrative state of the Reachable Address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

isisRAAddrPrefix.name: isisRAAddrPrefix
isisRAAddrPrefix.description: The destination of this Reachable Address. This is an Address Prefix. This object follows the ReplaceOnlyWhileDisabled and ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

isisRAMapType.name: isisRAMapType
isisRAMapType.description: The type of mapping to be employed to ascertain the SNPA Address that should be used in forwarding PDUs for this Reachable Address prefix. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior. The following values of mapping type are defined: none: The mapping is null because the neighbor SNPA is implicit by nature of the subnetwork (e.g., a point-to-point linkage). explicit: The subnetwork addresses in the object isisRASNPAAddress are to be used. extractIDI: The SNPA is embedded in the IDI of the destination NSAP Address. The mapping algorithm extracts the SNPA to be used according to the format and encoding rules of ISO8473/Add2. This SNPA extraction algorithm can be used in conjunction with Reachable Address prefixes from the X.121, F.69, E.163, and E.164 addressing subdomains. extractDSP: All, or a suffix, of the SNPA is embedded in the DSP of the destination address. This SNPA extraction algorithm extracts the embedded subnetwork addressing information by performing a logical AND of the isisRASNPAMask object value with the destination address. The part of the SNPA extracted from the destination NSAP is appended to the isisRASNPAPrefix object value to form the next hop subnetwork addressing information.

isisRAMetric.name: isisRAMetric
isisRAMetric.description: The metric value for reaching the specified prefix over this circuit. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisRAMetricType.name: isisRAMetricType
isisRAMetricType.description: Indicates whether the metric is internal or external. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisRASNPAAddress.name: isisRASNPAAddress
isisRASNPAAddress.description: The SNPA Address to which a PDU may be forwarded in order to reach a destination that matches the address prefix of the Reachable Address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisRASNPAMask.name: isisRASNPAMask
isisRASNPAMask.description: A bit mask with 1 bit indicating the positions in the effective destination address from which embedded SNPA information is to be extracted. For the extraction, the first octet of the isisRASNPAMask object value is aligned with the first octet (AFI) of the NSAP Address. If the isisRASNPAMask object value and NSAP Address are of different lengths, the shorter of the two is logically padded with zeros before performing the extraction. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisRASNPAPrefix.name: isisRASNPAPrefix
isisRASNPAPrefix.description: A fixed SNPA prefix for use when the isisRAMapType is extractDSP. The SNPA Address to use is formed by concatenating the fixed SNPA prefix with a variable SNPA part that is extracted from the effective destination address. For Reachable Address prefixes in which the entire SNPA is embedded in the DSP, the SNPA Prefix shall be null. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisRAType.name: isisRAType
isisRAType.description: The type of Reachable address. Those of type manual are created by the network manager. Those of type automatic are created through propagation of routing information from another routing protocol (e.g., IDRP).

isisIPRATable.name: isisIPRATable
isisIPRATable.description: The table of IP Reachable Addresses to networks, subnetworks, or hosts either manually configured or learned from another protocol.

isisIPRAEntry.name: isisIPRAEntry
isisIPRAEntry.description: Each entry defines an IP Reachable Address to a network, subnetwork, or host. Each IP Reachable Address may have multiple entries in the table, one for each equal cost path to the reachable address. Dynamically created rows MUST survive an agent reboot. Implementers need to be aware that if the total number of elements (octets or sub-identifiers) in isisIPRADestr, isisIPRADestPrefixLen, and isisIPRANextHopIndex is too great, then OIDs of column instances in this table will have more than 128 subidentifiers and cannot be accessed using SNMPv1, SNMPv2c, or SNMPv3.

isisIPRADestType.name: isisIPRADestType
isisIPRADestType.description: The type of this IP Reachable Address.

isisIPRADest.name: isisIPRADest
isisIPRADest.description: The destination of this IP Reachable Address. This is a network address, subnetwork address, or host address. The type of this address is determined by the value of the isisIPRADestType object.

isisIPRADestPrefixLen.name: isisIPRADestPrefixLen
isisIPRADestPrefixLen.description: The length of the IP Netmask for Reachability Address. The values for the index objects isisIPRADest and isisIPRADestPrefixLen must be consistent. When the value of isisIPRADest (excluding the zone index, if one is present) is x, then the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the mask formed from the corresponding index object isisIPRADestPrefixLen MUST be equal to x. If not, then the index pair is not consistent, and an inconsistentName error must be returned on SET or CREATE requests.

isisIPRANextHopIndex.name: isisIPRANextHopIndex
isisIPRANextHopIndex.description: Index of next hop. Used when there are multiple Equal Cost Multipath alternatives for the same destination.

isisIPRANextHopType.name: isisIPRANextHopType
isisIPRANextHopType.description: The type of the IP next hop address.

isisIPRANextHop.name: isisIPRANextHop
isisIPRANextHop.description: The IP next hop to this destination. The type of this address is determined by the value of the isisIPRANextHopType object.

isisIPRAType.name: isisIPRAType
isisIPRAType.description: The type of this IP Reachable Address. Those of type manual are created by the network manager. Those of type automatic are created through propagation of routing information from another routing protocol. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisIPRAExistState.name: isisIPRAExistState
isisIPRAExistState.description: The state of this IP Reachable Address. This object follows the ExistenceState and ManualOrAutomatic behaviors. Support for 'createAndWait' and 'notInService' is not required. A row entry cannot be modified when the value of this object is 'active'.

isisIPRAAdminState.name: isisIPRAAdminState
isisIPRAAdminState.description: The administrative state of the IP Reachable Address. This object follows the IsisAdminState and ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

isisIPRAMetric.name: isisIPRAMetric
isisIPRAMetric.description: The metric value for reaching the specified destination over this circuit. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisIPRAMetricType.name: isisIPRAMetricType
isisIPRAMetricType.description: Indicates whether the metric is internal or external. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisIPRAFullMetric.name: isisIPRAFullMetric
isisIPRAFullMetric.description: The wide metric value for reaching the specified destination over this circuit. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisIPRASNPAAddress.name: isisIPRASNPAAddress
isisIPRASNPAAddress.description: The SNPA Address to which a PDU may be forwarded in order to reach a destination that matches this IP Reachable Address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisLSPSummaryEntry.name: isisLSPSummaryEntry
isisLSPSummaryEntry.description: Each entry provides a summary describing an LSP currently stored in the system. Dynamically learned rows will not survive an agent reboot.

isisLSPLevel.name: isisLSPLevel
isisLSPLevel.description: At which level does this LSP appear?

isisLSPID.name: isisLSPID
isisLSPID.description: The 8-byte LSP ID for this Link State PDU.

isisLSPSeq.name: isisLSPSeq
isisLSPSeq.description: The sequence number for this LSP.

isisLSPZeroLife.name: isisLSPZeroLife
isisLSPZeroLife.description: Is this LSP being purged by this system?

isisLSPChecksum.name: isisLSPChecksum
isisLSPChecksum.description: The 16-bit Fletcher Checksum for this LSP.

isisLSPLifetimeRemain.name: isisLSPLifetimeRemain
isisLSPLifetimeRemain.description: The remaining lifetime, in seconds, for this LSP.

isisLSPTLVTable.name: isisLSPTLVTable
isisLSPTLVTable.description: The table of LSPs in the database.

isisLSPTLVEntry.name: isisLSPTLVEntry
isisLSPTLVEntry.description: Each entry describes a TLV within an LSP currently stored in the system. Dynamically learned rows will not survive an agent reboot.

isisLSPTLVIndex.name: isisLSPTLVIndex
isisLSPTLVIndex.description: The index of this TLV in the LSP. The first TLV has index 1, and the Nth TLV has an index of N.

isisLSPTLVSeq.name: isisLSPTLVSeq
isisLSPTLVSeq.description: The sequence number for this LSP.

isisLSPTLVChecksum.name: isisLSPTLVChecksum
isisLSPTLVChecksum.description: The 16-bit Fletcher Checksum for this LSP.

isisNotificationSysLevelIndex.name: isisNotificationSysLevelIndex
isisNotificationSysLevelIndex.description: The system level for this notification.

isisNotificationCircIfIndex.name: isisNotificationCircIfIndex
isisNotificationCircIfIndex.description: The identifier of this circuit relevant to this notification.

isisPduLspId.name: isisPduLspId
isisPduLspId.description: An Octet String that uniquely identifies a Link State PDU.

isisPduFragment.name: isisPduFragment
isisPduFragment.description: Holds up to 64 initial bytes of a PDU that triggered the notification.

isisPduFieldLen.name: isisPduFieldLen
isisPduFieldLen.description: Holds the System ID length reported in PDU we received.

isisPduMaxAreaAddress.name: isisPduMaxAreaAddress
isisPduMaxAreaAddress.description: Holds the Max Area Addresses reported in a PDU we received.

isisPduProtocolVersion.name: isisPduProtocolVersion
isisPduProtocolVersion.description: Holds the Protocol version reported in PDU we received.

isisPduLspSize.name: isisPduLspSize
isisPduLspSize.description: Holds the size of LSP we received that is too big to forward.

isisPduOriginatingBufferSize.name: isisPduOriginatingBufferSize
isisPduOriginatingBufferSize.description: Holds the size of isisSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize advertised by the peer in the originatingLSPBufferSize TLV. If the peer does not advertise this TLV, this value is set to 0.

isisPduBufferSize.name: isisPduBufferSize
isisPduBufferSize.description: Holds the size of LSP received from peer.

isisPduProtocolsSupported.name: isisPduProtocolsSupported
isisPduProtocolsSupported.description: The list of protocols supported by an adjacent system. This may be empty.

isisAdjState.name: isisAdjState
isisAdjState.description: The current state of an adjacency.

isisErrorOffset.name: isisErrorOffset
isisErrorOffset.description: An offset to a problem in a PDU. If the problem is a malformed TLV, this points to the beginning of the TLV. If the problem is in the header, this points to the byte that is suspicious.

isisErrorTLVType.name: isisErrorTLVType
isisErrorTLVType.description: The type for a malformed TLV.

isisDatabaseOverload.name: isisDatabaseOverload
isisDatabaseOverload.description: This notification is generated when the system enters or leaves the Overload state. The number of times this has been generated and cleared is kept track of by isisSysStatLSPDbaseOloads.

isisManualAddressDrops.name: isisManualAddressDrops
isisManualAddressDrops.description: This notification is generated when one of the manual areaAddresses assigned to this system is ignored when computing routes. The object isisNotificationAreaAddress describes the area that has been dropped. The number of times this event has been generated is counted by isisSysStatManAddrDropFromAreas. The agent must throttle the generation of consecutive isisManualAddressDrops notifications so that there is at least a 5-second gap between notifications of this type. When notifications are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time.

isisCorruptedLSPDetected.name: isisCorruptedLSPDetected
isisCorruptedLSPDetected.description: This notification is generated when we find that an LSP that was stored in memory has become corrupted. The number of times this has been generated is counted by isisSysCorrLSPs. We forward an LSP ID. We may have independent knowledge of the ID, but in some implementations there is a chance that the ID itself will be corrupted.

isisAttemptToExceedMaxSequence.name: isisAttemptToExceedMaxSequence
isisAttemptToExceedMaxSequence.description: When the sequence number on an LSP we generate wraps the 32-bit sequence counter, we purge and wait to re-announce this information. This notification describes that event. Since these should not be generated rapidly, we generate an event each time this happens. While the first 6 bytes of the LSPID are ours, the other two contain useful information.

isisIDLenMismatch.name: isisIDLenMismatch
isisIDLenMismatch.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with a different value for the System ID Length. This notification includes an index to identify the circuit where we saw the PDU and the header of the PDU, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. The agent must throttle the generation of consecutive isisIDLenMismatch notifications so that there is at least a 5-second gap between notifications of this type. When notifications are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time.

isisMaxAreaAddressesMismatch.name: isisMaxAreaAddressesMismatch
isisMaxAreaAddressesMismatch.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with a different value for the Maximum Area Addresses. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. The agent must throttle the generation of consecutive isisMaxAreaAddressesMismatch notifications so that there is at least a 5-second gap between notifications of this type. When notifications are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time.

isisOwnLSPPurge.name: isisOwnLSPPurge
isisOwnLSPPurge.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with our systemID and zero age. This notification includes the circuit Index and router ID from the LSP, if available, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion.

isisSequenceNumberSkip.name: isisSequenceNumberSkip
isisSequenceNumberSkip.description: When we receive an LSP with our System ID and different contents, we may need to reissue the LSP with a higher sequence number. We send this notification if we need to increase the sequence number by more than one. If two Intermediate Systems are configured with the same System ID, this notification will fire.

isisAuthenticationTypeFailure.name: isisAuthenticationTypeFailure
isisAuthenticationTypeFailure.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with the wrong authentication type field. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. The agent must throttle the generation of consecutive isisAuthenticationTypeFailure notifications so that there is at least a 5-second gap between notifications of this type. When notifications are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time.

isisAuthenticationFailure.name: isisAuthenticationFailure
isisAuthenticationFailure.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with an incorrect authentication information field. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. The agent must throttle the generation of consecutive isisAuthenticationFailure notifications so that there is at least a 5-second gap between notifications of this type. When notifications are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time.

isisVersionSkew.name: isisVersionSkew
isisVersionSkew.description: A notification sent when we receive a Hello PDU from an IS running a different version of the protocol. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. The agent must throttle the generation of consecutive isisVersionSkew notifications so that there is at least a 5-second gap between notifications of this type. When notifications are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time.

isisAreaMismatch.name: isisAreaMismatch
isisAreaMismatch.description: A notification sent when we receive a Hello PDU from an IS that does not share any area address. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. The agent must throttle the generation of consecutive isisAreaMismatch notifications so that there is at least a 5-second gap between notifications of this type. When notifications are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time.

isisRejectedAdjacency.name: isisRejectedAdjacency
isisRejectedAdjacency.description: A notification sent when we receive a Hello PDU from an IS but do not establish an adjacency for some reason. The agent must throttle the generation of consecutive isisRejectedAdjacency notifications so that there is at least a 5-second gap between notifications of this type. When notifications are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time.

isisLSPTooLargeToPropagate.name: isisLSPTooLargeToPropagate
isisLSPTooLargeToPropagate.description: A notification sent when we attempt to propagate an LSP that is larger than the dataLinkBlockSize for the circuit. The agent must throttle the generation of consecutive isisLSPTooLargeToPropagate notifications so that there is at least a 5-second gap between notifications of this type. When notifications are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time.

isisOrigLSPBuffSizeMismatch.name: isisOrigLSPBuffSizeMismatch
isisOrigLSPBuffSizeMismatch.description: A notification sent when a Level 1 LSP or Level 2 LSP is received that is larger than the local value for isisSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize, or when an LSP is received that contains the supported Buffer Size option and the value in the PDU option field does not match the local value for isisSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize. We pass up the size from the option field and the size of the LSP when one of them exceeds our configuration. The agent must throttle the generation of consecutive isisOrigLSPBuffSizeMismatch notifications so that there is at least a 5-second gap between notifications of this type. When notifications are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time.

isisProtocolsSupportedMismatch.name: isisProtocolsSupportedMismatch
isisProtocolsSupportedMismatch.description: A notification sent when a non-pseudonode segment 0 LSP is received that has no matching protocols supported. This may be because the system does not generate the field, or because there are no common elements. The list of protocols supported should be included in the notification: it may be empty if the TLV is not supported, or if the TLV is empty. The agent must throttle the generation of consecutive isisProtocolsSupportedMismatch notifications so that there is at least a 5-second gap between notifications of this type. When notifications are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time.

isisAdjacencyChange.name: isisAdjacencyChange
isisAdjacencyChange.description: A notification sent when an adjacency changes state, entering or leaving state up. The first 6 bytes of the isisPduLspId are the SystemID of the adjacent IS. The isisAdjState is the new state of the adjacency.

isisLSPErrorDetected.name: isisLSPErrorDetected
isisLSPErrorDetected.description: This notification is generated when we receive an LSP with a parse error. The isisCircIfIndex holds an index of the circuit on which the PDU arrived. The isisPduFragment holds the start of the LSP, and the isisErrorOffset points to the problem. If the problem is a malformed TLV, isisErrorOffset points to the start of the TLV, and isisErrorTLVType holds the value of the type. If the problem is with the LSP header, isisErrorOffset points to the suspicious byte. The number of such LSPs is accumulated in isisSysStatLSPErrors.

isisCompliance.name: isisCompliance
isisCompliance.description: The compliance statement for agents that support the IS-IS MIB. There are a number of INDEX objects that cannot be represented in the form of OBJECT clauses in SMIv2, but for which there are compliance requirements. Those requirements and similar requirements for related objects are expressed below, in pseudo-OBJECT clause form, in this description: -- OBJECT isisSummAddressType -- SYNTAX InetAddressType { ipv4(1), ipv6(2) } -- -- DESCRIPTION -- The MIB requires support for IPv4 Summary -- Addresses and anticipates the support of -- IPv6 addresses. -- -- -- OBJECT isisRedistributeAddrType -- SYNTAX InetAddressType { ipv4(1), ipv6(2) } -- -- DESCRIPTION -- The MIB requires support for IPv4 -- Redistribution Addresses and anticipates -- the support of IPv6 addresses.

isisReadOnlyCompliance.name: isisReadOnlyCompliance
isisReadOnlyCompliance.description: When this MIB is implemented without support for read-create (i.e., in read-only mode), the implementation can claim read-only compliance. Such a device can then be monitored but cannot be configured with this MIB.
